Police in Cape Town have arrested a 26-year-old shopkeeper for allegedly being in possession of an illegal firearm and ammunition, Western Cape police said on Saturday. In our efforts to bring the perpetrators of crime to justice and create a safe and secure environment for all people in our province, police attached to the Western Cape public order police conducted stop-and-search operations in Nkanini, Harare, in Khayelitsha, Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana said. They arrested a 26-year-old man in his shop after he was found in possession of an unlicensed .38 special revolver and five live rounds. The man would appear in the Khayelitsha Magistrate s Court on Tuesday on a charge of illegal possession of a firearm and ammunition, Rwexana said. African News Agency (ANA)